The paper deals with coding theory, specifically cyclic codes and BCH codes, which are commonly used in communication systems and storage devices. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions an application of the codes in secret sharing, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves computations and analysis of the codes, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with finite fields, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
